ü§ØPlay this video again and let the golden truth of the Medicine Man sink in‚Ä¶

Light slave tendencies?

üôãüèΩ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èGuilty.

For 50 years I have been so proud to wear the badge ‚Äúselfless‚Äù. And then at 50 years and 2 months, I also earned the badge ‚Äúburntout‚Äù.

I had a whole slew of accomplishments and slayed goals. As soon as one goal was checked off, another one populated. There I was‚Ä¶ corporate-dropout-turned-consultant-turned-coach. I had conquered the coveted business that generates over a million $ annually‚Ä¶ and had my eye on million $ months.

But then I started to realize that I, the me deep inside, was getting lost in the process. Sure, I could grind out the goal as I always have, but I had a knowing that I would get lost and/or sacrifice too much along the way‚Ä¶ and for what?!

So I‚Äôve been learning about integrating feminine energy into my being vs being so heavy with the masculine (results, data, logic, planning, organizing, etc). Thankful to have powerful voices in my corner illuminating the way and walking the path.

Yet ANOTHER message from the Universe that doing more and continuously prioritizing others and not prioritizing one‚Äôs own desires, needs, just is NOT the way!

We are taught to ‚Äúoutsource‚Äù. As in seeking love, worth, value, permission, validation, etc in others versus ‚Äúself sourcing‚Äù as in leaning into our selves, our own truths, and having foundations of self love and self worth.

Outsourcing is a never ending, frustrating, exhausting game jumping through hoops trying to please others or live according to societal expectations and constructs. It‚Äôs a root clause of burnout and feeling unfulfilled (kinda makes sense!)

Self sourcing is a never ending flow of energy, life becomes effortless, and feels oh so easy!

BONUS: when you fill your cup first then you are more potent serving others. To rephrase the Medicine Man‚Ä¶ a light worker is FAR more potent than a light slave.

This message from an Egyptian medicine man that we visited on our pilgrimage HIT. 12 of us said ‚ÄúYES‚Äù to ourselves and took a journey to explore and connect with the Divine Feminine‚Äî a source of power that we aren‚Äôt typically taught and rarely get to witness (at least relative to what we typically see which is wounded feminine and masculine).

You‚Äôre a heart-centered leader, I got that. But are you a light worker serving others as you embody what‚Äôs possible? Or are you more of a light slave?

Either way, I love you üòò
LL
